mtt <mtt@tichy.de>

Unix:
-----

1. Put the smapi package in the directory where the other packages of fidolinux
   reside:

   /usr/src/packages/		-> fidoconfig/
				-> hpt/
				-> smapi/

2. compile smapi

3. copy the library libsmapilnx.so.2.0 to a dir like /usr/local/lib

4. create syslinks:
	[cd /usr/local/lib]
	ln -s libsmapilnx.so.2.0 libsmapilnx.so.2
	ln -s libsmapilnx.so.2 libsmapilnx.so

You're ready. Now you can install hpt and other software which require smapi
like fidoconfig and the upcoming KFidoEd.
